# Add New Minimal API Endpoint

Create a new endpoint in `Program.cs` following these requirements:

## Endpoint Requirements
1. Use minimal API syntax with route handler
2. Choose appropriate HTTP method (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
3. Accept appropriate parameters:
   - `IFormFile` for file uploads
   - Request DTO (record type) for JSON bodies
   - Route parameters for resource identifiers
   - Query parameters for filtering/pagination
4. Apply `.DisableAntiforgery()` if accepting file uploads
5. Validate all inputs before processing
6. Return 400 Bad Request for invalid inputs with descriptive messages
7. Use injected service from DI for business logic
8. Return `TypedResults` with appropriate status codes
9. Add OpenAPI documentation attributes

## Template Structure
```csharp
/// <summary>
/// Brief description of what the endpoint does.
/// </summary>
app.MapPost("/resource-name", async (Parameters parameters, IService service) =>
{
    // Validation
    if (/* invalid input */)
        return TypedResults.BadRequest(new { error = "Descriptive message" });
    
    // Business logic through service
    var result = await service.ProcessAsync(parameters);
    
    // Return result
    return TypedResults.Ok(result);
})
.DisableAntiforgery() // Only for file uploads
.Produces<ResponseType>(200)
.ProducesProblem(400)
.ProducesProblem(500)
.WithName("EndpointName")
.WithOpenApi();
```

## File Upload Endpoint Template
```csharp
/// <summary>
/// Uploads and processes a file.
/// </summary>
app.MapPost("/upload", async (IFormFile file, IService service) =>
{
    // Validate file
    if (file is null or { Length: 0 })
        return TypedResults.BadRequest(new { error = "No file uploaded" });
    
    if (!file.FileName.EndsWith(".pdf", StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase))
        return TypedResults.BadRequest(new { error = "Only PDF files are supported" });
    
    // Process file
    var (result, error, statusCode) = service.ProcessFile(file);
    
    if (error != null)
        return TypedResults.Problem(error, statusCode: statusCode);
    
    return TypedResults.Ok(new { result });
})
.DisableAntiforgery()
.Produces<object>(200)
.ProducesProblem(400)
.ProducesProblem(500)
.WithName("UploadFile")
.WithOpenApi();
```

## JSON Endpoint Template
```csharp
public record CreateResourceRequest(string Name, string Description);
public record ResourceResponse(int Id, string Name, string Description);

/// <summary>
/// Creates a new resource.
/// </summary>
app.MapPost("/resources", async (CreateResourceRequest request, IResourceService service) =>
{
    // Validate
    if (string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(request.Name))
        return TypedResults.BadRequest(new { error = "Name is required" });
    
    // Create resource
    var resource = await service.CreateAsync(request);
    
    return TypedResults.Created($"/resources/{resource.Id}", resource);
})
.Produces<ResourceResponse>(201)
.ProducesProblem(400)
.WithName("CreateResource")
.WithOpenApi();
```

## Checklist
- [ ] XML summary comment added
- [ ] Input validation implemented
- [ ] Service injected and called
- [ ] TypedResults used for all return paths
- [ ] Produces/ProducesProblem attributes added
- [ ] WithName() for route naming
- [ ] WithOpenApi() for Swagger
- [ ] DisableAntiforgery() if file upload
- [ ] Error handling with appropriate status codes
